summary.en: Situated in the shadow of St Paul's Cathedral, Paternoster Chop House offers a robust traditional British menu in the heart of London's bustling Square Mile. As the seasons change so does the menu. The selection of fish changes daily, arriving each morning from the south west coast, caught from small day-boats that return to shore daily. Meat is butchered in-house by the master butcher, so a wide range of cuts and cooking styles are offered.

For global travelers with a cultured palate and a love of variety, Asia de Cuba restaurant, overseen by renowned international restaurateur Jeffrey Chodorow, combines elements of Asian and Cuban cuisine served sharing-style in a high energy London restaurant. Housed in a dramatically colonnaded space, Asia de Cuba's innovative menu is matched in its surroundings by a dramatic series of soaring art columns.

Bluebird Chelsea is a local neighbourhood restaurant on a grand scale, set in the heart of London's bustling Kings Road. With a restaurant, bar, caf√©, courtyard, food store, wine cellar, 4 private rooms and a bakery, there is something for everyone.

Overlooking the Thames, Blueprint Caf√© offers a bright and airy space complete with its own terrace. Benefiting from a private entrance, views of Tower Bridge to the West and Canary Wharf to the East, this unrivalled setting is matched only by its exquisite food with an emphasis on seasonality. During the warmer months, the restaurant‚Äôs glass doors open to create a sense of alfresco dining on the water. With floor to ceiling windows come rain or shine you can soak up the incredible views. Serving modern European cuisine, our chef Joseph Albina design a menu daily using fresh and seasonal ingredients carefully sourced from local farms and suppliers in the British Isles. The extensive wine list at Blueprint Caf√© explores the natural side of wines and comparing them to the traditional styles. Introducing large format bottles in Blueprint Caf√©. Blueprint Caf√© is the ideal location for all occasions, from business lunches to family gatherings, an intimate table for two to groups and private events.

A corner of Italian sunshine in Butlers Wharf, Shad Thames, Cantina del Ponte offers the influences, flavours and atmosphere of Italy. A huge canopy provides a people-watching paradise for sunny days with great views of Tower Bridge. Simple, regional and authentic Italian fare is aplenty. Feast on homemade pasta, delicious seafood and slow-cooked meat dishes, all accompanied by an extensive Italian wine list.

For lovers of classic English food, the Butlers Wharf Chop House is the perfect ticket. Fish & chips, steak & kidney pudding, plaice, sole and many others can be enjoyed in a spacious restaurant that is reminiscent of a boating shed.

When the weather cheers up, we have our long terrace which provides spectacular views of Tower Bridge and the Thames.

The Chop House also has its own bar, where one can have pre dinner drinks or perhaps enjoy a quick bite, this is a more informal, smaller part of the restaurant, that still boasts a quaint part of the Chop House terrace and great views. Set price lunch & dinner menus offer superb value for money.

Suave and sophisticated, The Cinnamon Club prides itself on a culinary craftsmanship that has won it multiple awards and an established position on the London dining scene.

Occupying the Grade II listed former Westminster Library, the restaurant radiates a studiously colonial air, right down to its lofty ceilings and book-lined walls. An imaginative approach to Indian haute cuisine results in constantly evolving multi-layered dishes, including a stunning gastronomic six-course banquet. Choosing to innovate rather than remain complacent, The Cinnamon Club invites you to sample speciality dishes such as Norwegian King Crab Claw with coconut, mace and cardamom, Bombay Spiced Vegetables with cumin pao, and Fillet Steak of Wagyu Beef with stir-fried morels and saffron sauce.

The extensive wine list can match any meal perfectly and the bar has a selection of speciality drinks to choose from, including Saffron Passion, Rose Petal and Pear Lassis. A sought-after destination for business dining, The Cinnamon Club is just a brief stroll away from some of London's most famous landmarks including Westminster Abbey, the Houses of Parliament and the London Eye.

Coq d'Argent serves classic French food in its spectacular rooftop setting at No.1 Poultry in the City of London. In addition to the main restaurant, the brasserie offers a less formal menu at lunchtime, while the outdoor terraces and gardens provide a verdant oasis in the heart of the Square Mile.

locations.regionNameLong: Le Pont de la Tour, London

summary.en: Le Pont de la Tour is a jewel in the crown of the London restaurant scene - a stylish, luxurious, bubbling restaurant that gives diners superb food and service set against unparalleled views of Tower Bridge, the Gherkin and the London skyline, During the day you can enjoy traditional French cooking with a modern twist in the calm of its marine-inspired interior. At dinner, the opulence and elegance of the main dining room awakens against the backdrop of floodlit Tower Bridge. Le Pont de la Tour's master sommelier Nicolas Clerc is an award-winning expert - Ruinart's Sommelier of the Year in 2007 - who oversees an impressive collection of Old and New World wines, including some rare Grand Crus.
